00:09:30.571 --> 00:09:31.705 position:21% line:89% align:start
Then that would mean.

00:09:32.206 --> 00:09:34.375 position:30% line:83% align:start
Don't you think
that's so impressive?

00:09:34.708 --> 00:09:37.344 position:27% line:83% align:start
I feel kinda bad
for the other rookies.

00:09:37.512 --> 00:09:38.679 position:41% line:89% align:start
[grins]

00:09:38.813 --> 00:09:40.281 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHINOZAKI]
She's who I felt bad for!

00:09:40.414 --> 00:09:43.184 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Something wrong?
-Nope, everything's fine!

00:09:43.751 --> 00:09:45.186 position:16% line:83% align:start
[TAKATSUKASA] Akina and I
joined the company

00:09:45.319 --> 00:09:47.321 position:13% line:83% align:start
at the same time, and we've
been spurring each other

00:09:47.455 --> 00:09:48.589 position:24% line:89% align:start
forward ever since.

00:09:49.090 --> 00:09:51.759 position:16% line:83% align:start
Even though he's the one
who always came out on top,

00:09:51.892 --> 00:09:54.295 position:19% line:83% align:start
his proposal that year
was amazing.

00:09:55.029 --> 00:09:56.897 position:27% line:83% align:start
Then the product
became a huge hit.

00:09:57.364 --> 00:09:58.966 position:30% line:83% align:start
And ever since,
I've had my hands full

00:09:59.100 --> 00:10:01.001 position:7% line:89% align:start
just trying to catch up to him.

00:10:02.303 --> 00:10:05.606 position:13% line:83% align:start
But now, I've made history
with how far I've come here,

00:10:06.474 --> 00:10:09.343 position:13% line:83% align:start
and he's gotten comfortable
with not making waves

00:10:10.144 --> 00:10:11.979 position:13% line:89% align:start
But I remember those times.

00:10:12.713 --> 00:10:14.148 position:7% line:89% align:start
We were at the top of our game,

00:10:14.281 --> 00:10:17.118 position:16% line:83% align:start
always pushing each other
to reach our full potential.

00:10:18.686 --> 00:10:20.121 position:21% line:89% align:start
And now I've realized

00:10:20.988 --> 00:10:22.957 position:10% line:89% align:start
to help me grow, I need him!

00:10:23.624 --> 00:10:24.792 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHINOZAKI]
Huh?

00:10:25.259 --> 00:10:27.261 position:19% line:83% align:start
[TAKATSUKASA] So I went
to the president with a plan.

00:10:27.962 --> 00:10:28.996 position:35% line:83% align:start
[PRESIDENT]
Very well then.

00:10:29.598 --> 00:10:33.033 position:13% line:83% align:start
If Kurusu can win the most
promising new hire contest,

00:10:33.167 --> 00:10:36.203 position:10% line:83% align:start
I will consider transferring
Akina to your department.

00:10:37.071 --> 00:10:38.239 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHINOZAKI]
Uh!

00:10:38.439 --> 00:10:40.674 position:16% line:83% align:start
So, I'm not trying to win
a trip anymore.

00:10:40.875 --> 00:10:42.409 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm trying to keep my manager!

00:10:43.177 --> 00:10:45.212 position:7% line:89% align:start
So, he's a damsel in distress.

00:10:45.346 --> 00:10:47.448 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're doing the opposite
of helping!

00:10:47.616 --> 00:10:49.083 position:38% line:83% align:start
I thought
that it might be unfair

00:10:49.216 --> 00:10:51.085 position:10% line:83% align:start
if you didn't know the stakes
you were playing for.

00:10:51.418 --> 00:10:53.854 position:38% line:83% align:start
Although,
there's no chance you'll win,

00:10:54.054 --> 00:10:55.590 position:13% line:89% align:start
so don't feel too torn up.

00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:57.391 position:16% line:89% align:start
Let's get going, Kurusu.

00:10:57.825 --> 00:10:59.628 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[KURUSU] Right.
-Hold on a second!

00:11:00.194 --> 00:11:02.129 position:33% line:83% align:start
I don't care
if you think you need him.

00:11:02.796 --> 00:11:04.298 position:24% line:89% align:start
I won't let him go.

00:11:04.566 --> 00:11:06.535 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm going to win that contest.

00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:08.969 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh. I know that look.

00:11:09.403 --> 00:11:11.405 position:33% line:83% align:start
You're ready
for the next stage.

00:11:11.972 --> 00:11:14.441 position:38% line:83% align:start
[giggles]
However.

00:11:14.708 --> 00:11:16.243 position:19% line:89% align:start
I will never be beaten.

00:11:16.911 --> 00:11:18.245 position:30% line:89% align:start
Not by anybody.

00:11:19.046 --> 00:11:21.248 position:19% line:83% align:start
This victory is as good
as mine.

00:11:21.650 --> 00:11:22.883 position:47% line:89% align:start
Uh.

00:11:24.051 --> 00:11:25.786 position:35% line:83% align:start
[chuckles]
And it's the first of many,

00:11:26.353 --> 00:11:29.223 position:21% line:83% align:start
because we're aiming
for even greater heights.

00:11:29.890 --> 00:11:31.125 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmph.

00:11:31.425 --> 00:11:32.459 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmph.

00:11:33.562 --> 00:11:34.828 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:11:35.329 --> 00:11:38.699 position:7% line:83% align:start
Dude, it got so real, they made
a breeze come out of nowhere.

00:11:38.832 --> 00:11:39.967 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:11:40.100 --> 00:11:41.902 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIYAMA]
I couldn't agree more!

00:11:42.736 --> 00:11:45.039 position:7% line:89% align:start
That was fantastic, Shinozaki!

00:11:45.372 --> 00:11:46.941 position:24% line:83% align:start
A powerful display
of subordinates

00:11:47.074 --> 00:11:50.144 position:16% line:83% align:start
engaged in heated battle
on behalf of their bosses!

00:11:50.579 --> 00:11:52.179 position:19% line:89% align:start
What a sight to behold.

00:11:53.013 --> 00:11:55.449 position:19% line:83% align:start
You should fight, too.
Do it for me, bro!

00:11:55.849 --> 00:11:57.484 position:7% line:89% align:start
Even if I cared, I still can't

00:11:57.619 --> 00:11:58.786 position:16% line:89% align:start
because no one wants you.

00:11:59.086 --> 00:12:01.722 position:38% line:83% align:start
Hot dog!
What a wild turn of events!

00:12:01.855 --> 00:12:03.057 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm so excited!

00:12:03.290 --> 00:12:04.725 position:38% line:83% align:start
[YUUSUKE]
Did you hear a word I said?

00:12:04.858 --> 00:12:06.260 position:27% line:89% align:start
A battle over me!

00:12:06.393 --> 00:12:07.962 position:10% line:83% align:start
-[YUUSUKE] No one said that.
-Godspeed out there.

00:12:08.095 --> 00:12:09.664 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHINOZAKI]
No matter how impossible,

00:12:10.164 --> 00:12:12.266 position:13% line:89% align:start
I can't lose this contest!

00:12:15.169 --> 00:12:17.438 position:13% line:83% align:start
Manager, can I talk to you
about something important?

00:12:17.606 --> 00:12:19.574 position:41% line:83% align:start
[AKINA]
Well, would you look at that!

00:12:19.708 --> 00:12:21.308 position:10% line:89% align:start
My tea stalk is standing up!

00:12:21.576 --> 00:12:24.546 position:7% line:83% align:start
Oh, they say that that's a sign
of good luck, y'know!

00:12:24.845 --> 00:12:26.013 position:27% line:89% align:start
I would hope so!

00:12:26.180 --> 00:12:28.550 position:19% line:83% align:start
Maybe we should do this
more often?

00:12:28.683 --> 00:12:29.750 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'd love that!

00:12:29.984 --> 00:12:31.553 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHINOZAKI]
They're so oblivious.

00:12:32.721 --> 00:12:35.990 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SHIORI] My Tiny Senpai
will be right back after this.

00:12:38.560 --> 00:12:40.995 position:7% line:83% align:start
I hope that you'll play with me
a whole lot!

00:12:41.262 --> 00:12:42.930 position:24% line:83% align:start
[WALLA KIDS] Okay!
[SHINOZAKI] Okay!

00:12:43.797 --> 00:12:45.533 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

